The document entitled "Notice to Homeowner" shall:
Contain the total sales price of the residence in default and an explanation of the distribution of the proceeds of the sale, including any payments to any parties, including the foreclosure consultant;
Be printed in 12 point type and written in the same language that is used by the homeowner and was used in discussions to describe the foreclosure consultant's or purchaser's services or to negotiate the transfer or sale of the property;
Be dated and personally signed by the homeowner and the purchaser and witnessed and acknowledged by a notary public appointed and commissioned by the State;
Describe in detail the terms of any sale or transfer including:
The name, business address, telephone number, and facsimile number of the person to whom the deed or title will be sold or transferred;
The address of the residence in default;
The total consideration to be given or received, directly or indirectly, by the homeowner, purchaser, and the foreclosure consultant;
The time at which title is to be sold or transferred to the purchaser; and
Any financial or legal obligations to which the homeowner may remain subject; and
Contain the following statement printed in at least 14 point boldface type and located in immediate proximity to the space reserved for the homeowner's signature:
